  "texts": [
    "Accordingly, it is not clear yet how people initiate an interaction with a virtual agent, and whether they convey their own intentions through action 1 3",
    "as they would do in front of a human confederate.",
    "In other words, it is not established yet if the fine kinematic variations associated with the expression of social intention observed during human-human interactions (see Becchio et al. 2008b; Gigliotti et al. 2020; Quesque et al. 2013 Quesque et al., 2016)) spontaneously transfer to human-virtual agent interactions.",
    "In order to address this issue, we conducted a first experiment (Experiment 1) in which participants were asked to grasp a dummy glass and place it in front of either a human confederate or a human-like virtual agent.",
    "Participants performed this grasp-to-place task with either a personal intention (to fill the glass themselves using a bottle) or a social intention (to have the glass filled by the human confederate or the virtual agent using the bottle)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "In other words, it is not established yet if the fine kinematic variations associated with the expression of social intention observed during human-human interactions (see Becchio et al. 2008b; Gigliotti et al. 2020; Quesque et al. 2013 Quesque et al., 2016)) spontaneously transfer to human-virtual agent interactions."
  ]
}